   {
      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "Actually it looks like relatives paths are supported for configuration options. -conf, -pid, and -wallet accept relative paths which are interpreted as relative to the data directory. (-wallet only supports relative paths)\n\nSo the current behavior seems to be consistent. It would be nice if it was documented somewhere that relative paths are interpreted as relative to the data directory, but I'm not sure where the best place to put that would be.\n",
